cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper addresses the problem of person re-identification, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a fully connected CRF model and uses it for efficient inference, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with image and video processing, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves some aspects of computer security, such as occlusion and background clutter, which are relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
